doc.ContractDescription: SAO WILL SUPPORT THE NASA JWST PROJECT OFFICE BY PROVIDING SUBJECT MATTER EXPERTISE DURING MEETINGS AND PERFORMING TASKS DIRECTLY RELATED TO THE JWST AND ITS SUBSYSTEMS, IN PARTICULAR THE OPTICAL TELESCOPE ELEMENT OTE. THESE TASKS WILL INCLUDE ADVISING THE GOVERNMENT ON THE PERFORMANCE OF THE OTE DESIGN, THE OTE MODELING EFFORT, THE INTEGRATION AND TEST VIBRATION, ACOUSTIC, CRYOGENIC AND OPTICAL FOR EACH PMSA, THE SMA, THE AOS, THE PATHFINDER OGSE 1,2 AND THE PMBSS. THE SAO TEAM WILL CONTINUE TO REVIEW THE PMBSS AS ITS DESIGN AND ASSEMBLY ENTERS ITS FINAL STAGES. DEVELOP HIGHLY SPECIALIZED MODELS AS NECESSARY TO VALIDATE LOCALIZED KEY DESIGN FEATURE AND OR WHERE ASSEMBLY HAS NOT BEEN ACCOMPLISHED TO PRINT. CONTINUE TO REVIEW STATIC TEST PLANS FOR THE PMBSS WINGS&CS BS. DEVELOP AND INTEGRATE HIGHLY SPECIALIZED MODELS TO VERIFY THAT THE PMBSS WINGS&CS BSF ARE BEING TESTED TO 1.25 DLL. CONTINUE TO DEVELOP PLANS FOR PATHFINDER OGSE 1, 2 ADJUNCT OPTICAL METROLOGY. CONTINUE TO REVIEW TEST PLANS FOR ALL OPTICAL, CRYOGENIC, VIBRATION ACOUSTIC AND STRENGTH TESTS. USING OUR HIGHLY SPECIALIZED INDEPENDENT MODELS, VERIFY THE OTE&OBS TEST OBJECTIVES WILL BE MET. CONTINUE TO PREPARE OPTICAL AND STRESS BASED PREDICTIONS FOR ALL OF THE ABOVE TESTS USING SAOS INDEPENDENTLY CREATED FEMS USING GFE CFE THERMAL DATA, CREATE IN SITU PREDICTIONS FOR ALL OTE CRYOGENIC TESTS AND COMPARE TO TEST DATA. PROVIDE HIGHLY SPECIALIZED THERMAL MODELS AND PREDICTIONS FOR THE PATHFINDER OGSE 1,2 NASA JSC TESTS. INTEGRATE SAO DERIVED MODELS WITH NASA JSC CHAMBER MODELS AND OTHER GSE MODELS TO PROVIDE A SINGLE, HIGHLY SPECIALIZED AND UNIQUE TEST MODE. PERFORM PATHFINDER THERMAL DISTORTION ANALYSIS USING OUR INDEPENDENT DEVELOPED HIGHLY SPECIALIZED FEMS. CONTINUE TO DOCUMENT ALL ACTIVITIES AND COMMUNICATE WITH THE GSFC JWST PROJECT PERSONNEL VIA ON SITE MEETINGS, TELEPHONE CONFERENCES, DETAILED TECHNICAL MEMOS&EMAILS.
